The Knoxville Gazette was the first newspaper published in the U.S. state of 
Tennessee and the third published west of the Appalachian Mountains. 
Established by George Roulstone (17671804) at the urging of Southwest 
Territory governor William Blount, the paper's first edition appeared on November 
5, 1791.
